  - content_for :cookies do
    %p
      GOV.UK puts small files (known as 'cookies') onto your computer to collect information about how you browse the
      site.
    %p Cookies are used to:
    %ul
      %li measure how you use the website so it can be updated and improved based on your needs
      %li remember the notifications you've seen so that we don't show them to you again
    %p
      %em GOV.UK cookies aren't used to identify you personally.
    %p You'll normally see a message on the site before we store a cookie on your computer.
    %p
      Find out more
      about #{link_to 'how to manage cookies', 'http://www.aboutcookies.org/', :class => 'external', :rel => 'external'}
      \.
    %h2 How cookies are used on GOV.UK
    %h3 Measuring website usage (Google Analytics)
    We use Google Analytics software to collect information about how you use GOV.UK. We do this to help make sure the site is meeting the needs of its users and to help us make improvements.
    %p Google Analytics stores information about:
    %ul
      %li the pages you visit on GOV.UK - how long you spend on each GOV.UK page
      %li how you got to the site
      %li what you click on while you're visiting the site.
    %p
      %em
        We don't collect or store your personal information so this information can't be used to identify who you are.
        For
        more information visit our #{link_to 'Privacy policy', :terms}.
    %p We don't allow Google to use or share our analytics data.
    %p Google Analytics sets the following cookies:
    %table.border
      %thead
        %tr
          %th Name
          %th Purpose
          %th Expires
      %tbody
        %tr
          %td
            %code _utma
          %td Determines the number of unique visitors to the site
          %td 2 years
        %tr
          %td
            %code _utmb
          %td This works with _utmc to calculate the average length of time you spend on our site
          %td 30 minutes
        %tr
          %td
            %code _utmc
          %td This works with _utmb to calculate when you close your browser
          %td when you close your browser
        %tr
          %td
            %code _utmz
          %td
            This provides information about how you reached the site (For example from another website or a search engine)
          %td 6 months
        %tr
          %td
            %code ga_nextpage_params
          %td This stores data to be sent to Google on the next page you request
          %td when you close your browser
        %tr
          %td
            %code GDS_successEvents and GDS_analyticsTokens
          %td These help us identify how you use GOV.UK so we can make the site better
          %td 4 months
        %tr
          %td
            %code _ga
          %td
            This is a google analytics cookie that helps us understand how the service is being used in detail. Your data is
            anonymised.
          %td 2 years
    %p
      You
      can #{link_to 'opt out of Google Analytics cookies', 'https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout', :class => 'external', :rel => 'external'}
      \.
    %h2 Our introductory message
    %p
      You may see a pop-up welcome message when you first visit GOV.UK. We'll store a cookie so that your computer knows
      you've seen it and knows not to show it again.
    %table.border
      %thead
        %tr
          %th Name
          %th Purpose
          %th Expires
      %tbody
        %tr
          %td
            %code seen_cookie_message
          %td Saves a message to let us know that you have seen our cookie message
          %td 1 month
